@startuml sqlite-in-git-fail
title SQLite-in-git: git treats the DB as a binary blob

skinparam monochrome false
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Helvetica"
skinparam rectangle {
    BackgroundColor #FAFAFA
    BorderColor #666
    RoundCorner 6
}

rectangle "Agent A\nbd create 'X'\ncommit db.sqlite" as A #D9EDFF
rectangle "Agent B\nbd create 'Y'\ncommit db.sqlite" as B #D9EDFF

rectangle "git merge A + B\n\nCONFLICT (binary)\n- take A: lose B's task\n- take B: lose A's task\n- merge: impossible" as M #F5C2C7

A -down-> M
B -down-> M

note bottom of M
  git stores the whole .sqlite file each commit.
  A meaningful diff at the row level does not exist.
  Two concurrent writers = manual recovery every time.
end note

@enduml
